<item>
            <title>[MCHECKSTYLE-260] sourceDirectories property is ignored in multi-modules</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-260</link>
                <project id="12317223" key="MCHECKSTYLE">Maven Checkstyle Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a multi-module build which uses a plugin that generates code (xjc). The directory is added to the compile source directories.&lt;br/&gt;
With 2.13, this directory is by default scanned by checkstyle - but I want to exclude this.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems, that setting &lt;tt&gt;sourceDirectories&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t have any effect for the child modules.&lt;br/&gt;
Is this even the right approach to exclude a source root?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is an integration test. It just uses build-helper-maven-plugin to add an additional source folder.&lt;br/&gt;
The parent pom configures &lt;tt&gt;sourceDirectories&lt;/tt&gt; to be just &lt;tt&gt;${project.build.sourceDirectory&lt;/tt&gt;}. I would have expected, that checkstyle doesn&apos;t find any violations, as &lt;tt&gt;src/generated/java&lt;/tt&gt; shouldn&apos;t be checked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think, it&apos;s related with the change &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-70&quot; title=&quot;Support for multiple source folders&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MCHECKSTYLE-70&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MCHECKSTYLE-70&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It works with 2.12&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
