&lt;p&gt;Because of a bug in Sisu, plugin parameters of type Collection or array are always using their default value if it is specified (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-5440&quot; title=&quot;default-value on mojo parameter of type collection or array effectively make parameter read-only&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MNG-5440&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MNG-5440&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). This was fixed in 3.3.9, but to be able to have compatibility for all Maven 3.x versions, we have to handle the default value manually, instead of relying on @Parameter&apos;s defaultValue mechanism.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Updating the MavenProject stub tests so that they return meaningful values for compileSourceRoot and testCompileSourceRoot (thus getting rid of the specific code inside the actual Mojo checking for null when that cannot happen on a real project). (gboue: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/?view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1780622&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/?view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1780622&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
