&lt;p&gt;   **&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Andreas Dangel&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adangel)**&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adangel)**&lt;/a&gt; opened **&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-260&quot; title=&quot;sourceDirectories property is ignored in multi-modules&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MCHECKSTYLE-260&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MCHECKSTYLE-260&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-260?redirect=false)**&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-260?redirect=false)**&lt;/a&gt; and commented&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   I have a multi-module build which uses a plugin that generates code (xjc). The directory is added to the compile source directories.&lt;br/&gt;
   With 2.13, this directory is by default scanned by checkstyle - but I want to exclude this.&lt;br/&gt;
   It seems, that setting `sourceDirectories` doesn&apos;t have any effect for the child modules.&lt;br/&gt;
   Is this even the right approach to exclude a source root?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   Attached is an integration test. It just uses build-helper-maven-plugin to add an additional source folder.&lt;br/&gt;
   The parent pom configures `sourceDirectories` to be just `${project.build.sourceDirectory}`. I would have expected, that checkstyle doesn&apos;t find any violations, as `src/generated/java` shouldn&apos;t be checked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   I think, it&apos;s related with the change &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCHECKSTYLE-70&quot; title=&quot;Support for multiple source folders&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MCHECKSTYLE-70&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MCHECKSTYLE-70&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   It works with 2.12&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;   &amp;#8212;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   *&lt;b&gt;Affects:&lt;/b&gt;* 2.13&lt;/p&gt;

